  "notes": [
    {
      "title": "Lamentation (الندبة)",
      "titleArabic": "الندبة",
      "content": [
        "Lamentation (الندبة) is a special form of vocative used to express grief or sorrow over something lost.",
        "The particle وَا (wā) is used instead of يَا, and the noun is followed by أَلِف and هَاء (ـَاهْ)."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "وَا is the primary particle for lamentation",
        "Add ـَاهْ to the end of the lamented noun",
        "يَا can also be used in lamentation",
        "Used to express deep sorrow or loss"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "وَا مُحَمَّدَاهْ", "english": "Alas, Muhammad!" },
        { "arabic": "وَا أَبَاهُ", "english": "Alas, my father!" },
        { "arabic": "وَا حَسْرَتَاهْ", "english": "Alas, what regret!" },
        { "arabic": "وَا إِسْلَامَاهْ", "english": "Alas, Islam! (expressing concern)" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Seeking Help (الاستغاثة)",
      "titleArabic": "الاستغاثة",
      "content": [
        "The call for help (الاستغاثة) uses يَا followed by لَـ (lam) attached to the one being called for help.",
        "It expresses urgency and the need for assistance."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Structure: يَا + لَـ + the helper (مستغاث به)",
        "The one sought for help takes ـَ (fatha) on the final letter",
        "Can add لِـ before the cause of distress",
        "Used in situations of urgency and need"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "يَا لَلْمُسْلِمِينَ", "english": "O Muslims (help!)!" },
        { "arabic": "يَا لَلَّهِ", "english": "O God (help!)!" },
        { "arabic": "يَا لَلْعَجَبِ", "english": "How amazing! (lit. O wonder!)" },
        { "arabic": "يَا لَلْمُصِيبَةِ", "english": "What a disaster!" }
      ]
    }
  ],
